Hungary Code Changes

In coming metadata release: National prefix (06) will be present by default in national format for both fixed line and mobile numbers based on Wikipedia. So making the code ready.

For Hungary, there is special logic in formatNumberForMobileDialing() to manually add national prefix as earlier we are not adding based on metadata. So we are removing it as part of this change; and it is no more needed. Also removing the relevant test data and unit tests as because this is the only case tested for Hungary. More details in cl/265831383

Evidence: https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Telephone_numbers_in_Hungary

Mimics: https://github.com/google/libphonenumber/pull/2387

Update AsYouTypeFormatter for better format selection

AsYouTypeFormatter changed to better choose between rules when dialling locally; previously we used the international rules when the national prefix was present since this would exclude the local-only rules. However, there are some numbers that are not internationally diallable that *do* use the national prefix, and this logic precluded formatting them correctly.

See https://github.com/googlei18n/libphonenumber/pull/2272

Note: On the PHP side, this fixes issues with NumberFormat->hasDomesticCarrierCodeFormattingRule() only checking if the variable was set, rather than having content from metadata.

Merge branch 'reducePrefixMapperFileCount'

* reducePrefixMapperFileCount:
  Reduce NANPA countries into 2 digit prefixes
  Basic prefix expansion control for Prefix Data
  Handle English fallback for all languages
Reduce NANPA countries into 2 digit prefixes

Basic prefix expansion control for Prefix Data

By coming prefixes back to their original country code (China) for
everything but geolocation. The expansion of the prefix still happens
for NANPA countries and one Chinese prefix (+861) to reduce memory usage
for the total number of prefixes (~150,000). This primitive method might
need updating in the future as other prefixes get more data.

When loading the data, it now recursively searches the Prefix Map for
the whole phone number, instead of just the country code. Further
optimisations could be made here in the future to use array keys instead
of array values.

Handle English fallback for all languages

Previously, it would only search for the English fallback on files with 2 characters.

Mark Phonemetadata as @internal

Switch to possibleLengths metadata

Google notes:

Switching the internal implementation of isPossible and related functions
to use the new possibleLengths metadata. This affects a lot of countries,
making isPossible more restrictive as more precise data is available. It
also affects parsing ambiguous and invalid numbers, as we decide whether
to strip a possible national prefix (1) or country code based on the length
of the number and whether it is possible before or after this.
